{
  "texts": [
    "Similar trends are reported by Sasanipour et al. [43], who observed that a 10% replacement ratio increases workability by 15% and shortens the setting time by 10%.",
    "When the specific dosage is not mentioned, Ali et al. [44] and Wang et al.",
    "[45] noted improvements in workability (between 8 and 12%) and a reduction in bleeding (by 10% to 12%).",
    "In contrast, when silica fume is combined with nanosilica, it may slightly reduce workability by 5% while maintaining other fresh properties, as reported by Kim et al. [46].",
    "Additionally, research by Jeong et al. [47] indicates that variations in the setting time can occur, with a 5% to 10% SF content accelerating the initial setting time."
  ]
}